Quickstrike/Quasar:




Quickstrike didn't like to see Black Arachnia in stasis lock, but it 
looked like her systems were recooperating. He knelt down to her bunk 
side to stay with her.

He instantly forgot about the offspring, leaving her in the hallway 
for her own devises. He rested his head by Black Arachnia's putting 
his arm under his head to support it. He wanted to stay by her to 
make sure she came round. He was very protective of her. 

He closed his optics a few times and fell asleep.




Quasar looked over, and saw the arachnid pair resting. What was she 
supposed to do now? The male just told her to follow him, and he 
didn't say much afterwards. He never explained to her where she was, 
who she was, or what she was. Maybe that was suppose to be up to her. 
Or maybe she was supposed to wait.

There was something about the two that told her to wait for them. 
Slowly and quietly she walked into the room and sat down by the end 
of the bunk and leaned against it.
